00:52:01.360 --> 00:52:04.060
Can you tell folks a little
bit about those kind of studies

00:52:04.060 --> 00:52:05.840
and what you're doing and--

00:52:05.840 --> 00:52:06.340
- Sure.

00:52:06.340 --> 00:52:07.272
- --how those work?

00:52:07.272 --> 00:52:08.980
I think it's a really
interesting example

00:52:08.980 --> 00:52:10.250
of better data.

00:52:10.250 --> 00:52:10.750
- Sure.

00:52:10.750 --> 00:52:11.120
- Yeah.

00:52:11.120 --> 00:52:13.670
- And I'm happy to hear that
you have some experience with it

00:52:13.670 --> 00:52:14.170
as well.

00:52:14.170 --> 00:52:15.770
- Barely.

00:52:15.770 --> 00:52:16.270
- Yeah.

00:52:16.270 --> 00:52:18.250
So one of the main
starting points

00:52:18.250 --> 00:52:21.060
in this cohort study I
mentioned based in Rotterdam

00:52:21.060 --> 00:52:23.560
that I work with
is we're starting

00:52:23.560 --> 00:52:25.720
to have these kind
of app-based studies

00:52:25.720 --> 00:52:29.339
where we give participants
in our studies these

00:52:29.339 --> 00:52:31.630
prompts on their cell phone
to answer certain questions

00:52:31.630 --> 00:52:32.200
over time.

00:52:32.200 --> 00:52:33.700
And so just thinking
about something

00:52:33.700 --> 00:52:35.325
like eating disorders,
if you're trying

00:52:35.325 --> 00:52:37.150
to understand what
causes someone

00:52:37.150 --> 00:52:41.120
to engage in a compensatory
behavior today,

00:52:41.120 --> 00:52:43.630
and you're trying to
understand that behavior today,

00:52:43.630 --> 00:52:46.510
you want the context of
what happened on that day.

00:52:46.510 --> 00:52:48.400
And so these app-based
kind of things

00:52:48.400 --> 00:52:50.920
allow you to get real time
collection of that data

00:52:50.920 --> 00:52:53.080
rather than asking a
survey every two or three

00:52:53.080 --> 00:52:54.616
years or something like that.

00:52:54.616 --> 00:52:55.740
And so I think that-- yeah.

00:52:55.740 --> 00:52:58.690
There's a lot of opportunities
to refine your questions

00:52:58.690 --> 00:53:03.060
to ideas of what's happening
at the hourly limit,

00:53:03.060 --> 00:53:04.810
or the daily limit,
or things like that

00:53:04.810 --> 00:53:06.551
with these kinds of studies.

00:53:06.551 --> 00:53:07.050
- Yeah.

00:53:07.050 --> 00:53:09.010
So some of the things you can--

00:53:09.010 --> 00:53:12.220
we're doing a study that's
sort of similar to that,

00:53:12.220 --> 00:53:14.020
also looking at some
eating behaviors.

00:53:14.020 --> 00:53:17.440
You can look at perhaps what was
