these two social groups

01:08:03.140 --> 01:08:06.890
in particular ways, what would
the reduction and the disparity

01:08:06.890 --> 01:08:11.140
be, and have very explicit
intervention strategies.

01:08:11.140 --> 01:08:14.800
And that-- so sort of I
see as a winnowing down.

01:08:14.800 --> 01:08:16.760
So we have all these
targets, and then

01:08:16.760 --> 01:08:18.620
given sort of an
upper bound of what

01:08:18.620 --> 01:08:20.569
we could achieve by
removing disparities then

01:08:20.569 --> 01:08:24.620
we can actually get to finer
intervention strategies.

01:08:24.620 --> 01:08:28.520
Along the way, I think it's
important to also leverage

01:08:28.520 --> 01:08:32.779
actual policy changes
and actual interventions

01:08:32.779 --> 01:08:36.140
in natural experiments
to actually see

01:08:36.140 --> 01:08:39.630
what real interventions
have accomplished.

01:08:39.630 --> 01:08:42.170
And so I sort of take
these sorts of analyses

01:08:42.170 --> 01:08:46.778
as guiding our focus about what
to do follow-up studies on.

01:08:46.778 --> 01:08:48.319
And at the end of
the day, it's going

01:08:48.319 --> 01:08:51.680
to take real experiments
to actually get

01:08:51.680 --> 01:08:54.721
robust evidence for this.

