01:17:34.020 --> 01:17:35.760
versus safety and all of that.

01:17:35.760 --> 01:17:38.160
They're just trying to
give these estimates

01:17:38.160 --> 01:17:40.890
of how many lives could be
saved or how many injuries

01:17:40.890 --> 01:17:44.110
could be prevented
and trying to do that.

01:17:44.110 --> 01:17:46.980
And then I think when they
communicate that they really

01:17:46.980 --> 01:17:52.350
look for people in
the communities that

01:17:52.350 --> 01:17:54.472
can start having
that conversation

01:17:54.472 --> 01:17:56.430
and propagating the
conversation a little more.

01:17:56.430 --> 01:17:59.700
So focusing on parents of
kids, because everybody

01:17:59.700 --> 01:18:04.830
wants our kids to be safe, or
focusing on the instructors

01:18:04.830 --> 01:18:06.270
of gun safety courses.

01:18:06.270 --> 01:18:08.160
And I think that
that's maybe how

01:18:08.160 --> 01:18:11.790
you do it is it's an incremental
conversation that you have.

01:18:11.790 --> 01:18:14.040
But recognizing that you're
doing the best science

01:18:14.040 --> 01:18:17.520
you can do, and that's part
of a larger story of how

01:18:17.520 --> 01:18:18.830
we function as communities.

01:18:18.830 --> 01:18:21.758
Yeah.

01:18:21.758 --> 01:18:27.810
- [INAUDIBLE] with myself and
my colleagues [INAUDIBLE] So

01:18:27.810 --> 01:18:30.310
in South Africa, we worked with
the South African government

01:18:30.310 --> 01:18:30.810
quite a bit.

01:18:30.810 --> 01:18:33.400
So what has required
us to actually build

01:18:33.400 --> 01:18:37.260
that relationship well
is listening to them

01:18:37.260 --> 01:18:38.830
and not going in
there as a foreigner

01:18:38.830 --> 01:18:41.740
and forcing whatever
we've believed

01:18:41.740 --> 01:18:44.020
to be either an association
or something that's

01:18:44.020 --> 01:18:46.450
causal on them.

01:18:46.450 --> 01:18:48.750
So it is really listening
and having a conversation.

01:18:48.750 --> 01:18:54.310
And like you said, Sonya, is
doing it incrementally and not

01:18:54.310 --> 01:18:56.260
overloading people
with information,

01:18:56.260 --> 01:18:58.390
because it doesn't help.

01:18:58.390 --> 01:19:00.220
But we have-- it Took.

01:19:00.220 --> 01:19:02.497
A long time for us to
develop these relationships

01:19:02.497 --> 01:19:04.330
with the South African
government and people

01:19:04.330 --> 01:19:07.570
specifically in there
who will help to actually

01:19:07.570 --> 01:19:09.400
have an effect on policy.

01:19:09.400 --> 01:19:12.160
It's that conversation
that's been over the last

01:19:12.160 --> 01:19:14.470
probably decade that has
helped us really kind of

01:19:14.470 --> 01:19:19.414
communicate effectively and
change policy at that level.

01:19:19.414 --> 01:19:21.660
Yeah.

01:19:21.660 --> 01:19:24.210
- I just-- I have a
couple of thoughts.

01:19:24.210 --> 01:19:27.540
I don't have anything additional
to what's already been shared.

01:19:27.540 --> 01:19:29.680
I agree with that.

01:19:29.680 --> 01:19:33.780
At the hospital
where I work, the IRB

01:19:33.780 --> 01:19:36.120
has community members
that sit on it

01:19:36.120 --> 01:19:38.890
as well as studies
that we enroll.

01:19:38.890 --> 01:19:42.150
We usually try to have community
representation to ensure

01:19:42.150 --> 01:19:46.120
that it's asking a question
that people actually care about

01:19:46.120 --> 01:19:48.720
and that it's
represented accurately.

01:19:48.720 --> 01:19:52.080
And some-- just an
anecdote from my own work.

01:19:52.080 --> 01:19:54.390
Before I was doing
this, my dissertation

01:19:54.390 --> 01:19:59.040
was on vaccination and
vaccine-preventable diseases.

01:19:59.040 --> 01:20:02.370
And naive me thought that
everyone would just get

01:20:02.370 --> 01:20:05.250
vaccinated once they
saw this science, right?

01:20:05.250 --> 01:20:08.770
How can you argue against that?

01:20:08.770 --> 01:20:10.830
I'm no longer naive to that.

01:20:10.830 --> 01:20:14.320
And so one thing I think
we can do a better job--

01:20:14.320 --> 01:20:16.770
and I started to do
this-- was let's reach out

01:20:16.770 --> 01:20:19.260
to the anti-vaccination
community

01:20:19.260 --> 01:20:23.310
rather than just scoff at them.

01:20:23.310 --> 01:20:25.717
So I engaged one of
their representatives

01:20:25.717 --> 01:20:26.550
and said, all right.

01:20:26.550 --> 01:20:27.990
What do you propose?

01:20:27.990 --> 01:20:30.810
What do you want to have happen?

01:20:30.810 --> 01:20:34.740
If you are so adamant about
not getting vaccinated,

01:20:34.740 --> 01:20:35.670
what's your proposal?

01:20:35.670 --> 01:20:39.140
Because one thing we can all
agree on is that this is--

01:20:39.140 --> 01:20:41.160
I mean, we don't want--

01:20:41.160 --> 01:20:44.070
we don't want otherwise
preventable diseases

01:20:44.070 --> 01:20:46.471
from making a resurgence
as they're doing now.

01:20:46.471 --> 01:20:47.720
So what are your alternatives?

01:20:47.720 --> 01:20:50.760
It was really an
enlightening conversation

01:20:50.760 --> 01:20:53.490
that I had with this
person, and I actually

01:20:53.490 --> 01:20:56.730
wanted to write this
up and publish it

01:20:56.730 --> 01:20:57.840
in just like a magazine.

01:20:57.840 --> 01:20:59.730
Unfortunately I didn't
get permission from them,

01:20:59.730 --> 01:21:00.480
but it was still--

01:21:00.480 --> 01:21:02.210
I think that's
something that we can do

01:21:02.210 --> 01:21:03.900
is just reach out
and ensure that we

01:21:03.900 --> 01:21:07.470
have a balanced
viewpoint on things, too.

01:21:07.470 --> 01:21:09.420
That we're not just--
because in some ways,

01:21:09.420 --> 01:21:13.980
it is kind of insular in the
community that I work in.

01:21:13.980 --> 01:21:17.430
Like, everyone kind of thinks
alike in the public health

01:21:17.430 --> 01:21:20.180
program, and we all believe
that these are the interventions

01:21:20.180 --> 01:21:21.180
that people should have.

01:21:21.180 --> 01:21:24.030
But it's really interesting
when you get outside of that

01:21:24.030 --> 01:21:27.660
and talk to other people
that have just as strong--

01:21:27.660 --> 01:21:30.780
and are very eloquent
speakers as well--

01:21:30.780 --> 01:21:31.920
opinions to the contrary.

01:21:31.920 --> 01:21:36.030
It's very-- it's helpful to kind
of humble your work in a way

01:21:36.030 --> 01:21:36.550
as well.

01:21:36.550 --> 01:21:37.680
So I think that's--

01:21:37.680 --> 01:21:40.230
to me, at least, like having
community representation

01:21:40.230 --> 01:21:42.120
and having a
dialogue with people

01:21:42.120 --> 01:21:47.040
that are just outside
of your direct role.

